<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-19T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-19T12:00:00-05:00" n="452" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d452">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/142a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in the Netherlands</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-19T12:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 19, 1918, noon.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>924. Your 1899, January 17, 8 p.m. It is reported here that <hi rend="italic">Nieuw Amsterdam</hi> has sailed. If she has not
                                sailed, Department gives authority to you to give assurance that <hi rend="italic">Nieuw Amsterdam</hi> will be permitted to return
                                to Holland on a guarantee from the Dutch Government that she will
                                return immediately to the United States on her next arrival in
                                Holland. Department gives you this authority in order to facilitate
                                pending negotiations with the Dutch Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>